cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NA, cs.GR 

This paper deals with computational geometry and graph theory, specifically the β-skeleton of a point set. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the construction of a fractal, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of dilation and Gabriel graph suggests cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on graph theory and geometric algorithms could also place it under cs.GR (Graphics).
